  "text": "which implies that the way in which they effectuate their mathematically equivalent functions may also be quite different. This is investigated by calculating the motor displacements in the finger movements generated by keeping alternately one motor or joint isometric [as in [CITATION_1] ]. (14) it follows that their displacements differ only to the degree that rL1 > ril. Physically this is easily understood. With isometric deep flexor, the lumbrical origin is fixed, and can be imagined on the metacarpals, just as the interosseus. As the tendons of the interosseus and lumbrical are almost identical (the only difference being: rL1 > r11). their displacements are also almost equal.",
